{#
  Override of mkdocstrings-python's module template.

  Suppresses the docstring of the *root* module only — i.e. when a page does
  `::: viscy_data`, the package's own top-level docstring is not rendered, but
  the docstrings of its members (classes, functions) and of any submodules are
  left untouched. This keeps the per-package overview prose on the Markdown page
  (the "What's here" admonition) without duplicating the `__init__.py` docstring.

  `root` is the context flag mkdocstrings sets for the object the `:::`
  identifier points at.
#}
{% extends "_base/module.html.jinja" %}

{% block docstring scoped %}
  {% if not root %}{{ super() }}{% endif %}
{% endblock docstring %}
